Instructions: Router = L3 device (can be a 'switch'), Switch = L2 device
Select the most appropriate region for your device - this determines TACACS, DNS, and NTP servers.
Specify the source interface for TACACS, TFTP, Logging, NTP, SNMP (usually Loopback0 for routers, VlanX for switches)
This will Enable Multicast Globally for Routers - You still need to configure PIM on every interface that it is required - See Interfaces Tab
Use the ENCRYPTED password from the Vault.  NOT CLEAR TEXT
